n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#999999;\u0022\u003E(I joke. You can weigh in to say that you don\u0027t support this, and it won\u0027t be off topic.)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-11T17:25:11Z\u0022 title=\u002207/11/2017 05:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Dman979\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EChanged formating\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vinhero100","CreatedById":170677,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-11T17:26:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support This. This will save lots of DeltaV when getting into orbit, rather than wasting it on altitude...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-11T21:46:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499765525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157058\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal101\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Kerbal101 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/90252-13-pilot-assistant-atmospheric-piloting-aids-1132-may-28/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPilot Assistant\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E does exactly this and is also purposely limited to this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can hold - vertical speed (horizon), pitch (horizon), band, heading and also horizontal speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is no \u0022autopilot\u0022 in it, but exactly atmospheric hold functions. Extremely valuable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPA does much more than just horizon-relative \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, and anyone saying it\u0027s not an autopilot is kidding themselves.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree it\u0027s a great mod, sort of distilled out the plane-centric modes of MechJeb\u0027s SmartASS.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-12T07:05:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/12858-red-iron-crown/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002212858\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/12858-red-iron-crown/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Red Iron Crown\u003C/a\u003E it holds things by reading from sensors and applying change to controls, but I disagree about it doing what \u0022auto pilot\u0022 does: automatic landing, automatic start, traveling to location (at altitude/speed) are not included. I am only using it to hold vertical speed at 0 (which is what \u0022hold horizon is\u0022) to alt-tab into something else for half an hour. But one can certainly argue if an egg is a chicken \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have previously used other mod which actually implemented these more advanced things (went \u0022autopilot\u0022), which caused a lot of lag due to me battling through interface options for very basic stuff - sometimes enough to loose control, because entering values in fields locks keyboard input away from vehicle controls. There can be some complications when using mechanic \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/1sNMHdaJx5c?t=1m12s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESmartASS\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"53miner53","CreatedById":172955,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-12T15:19:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"User name","CreatedById":154075,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-13T03:36:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd to complement that, maybe there could also be a button to hold the rocket upwards- it would be useful for the beginning of low \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E launches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PaperAviator","CreatedById":177832,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-13T04:18:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(85,85,85);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EApoyo este.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(85,85,85);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#555555\u0022\u003EHow about adding an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E feature that keeps your current\u00A0angle (Pitch, yaw, etc)?\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(85,85,85);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(85,85,85);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#555555;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Speak\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-13T04:19:57Z\u0022 title=\u002207/13/2017 04:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by PaperAviator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"elektron2kim","CreatedById":177790,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-13T08:52:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s autopilot technology in the real world. Some aspects are done by trim hold of the control surfaces and flaps is a totally basic functionality on an airplane more than airbrakes and parachutes. A good step towards these potential implementations in KSP would be to hold the nose pointing at the horizon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-13T09:59:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223119449\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499919502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177832\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022PaperAviator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, PaperAviator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(85,85,85);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EApoyo este.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:rgb(85,85,85);\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#555555\u0022\u003EHow about adding an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E feature that keeps your current\u00A0angle (Pitch, yaw, etc)?\u0